-- Are our employees actually working to standard and working efficiently?
WITH efficiency_avgs AS (
SELECT 
dmm.driver_id,
CONCAT(dri.first_name, ' ', dri.last_name) AS full_name,
SUM(dmm.trips_completed) AS total_trips_completed,
ROUND(SUM(dmm.average_mpg * dmm.trips_completed) / SUM(dmm.trips_completed), 2) AS weighted_avg_mpg,
ROUND(SUM(dmm.average_idle_hours * dmm.trips_completed) / SUM(dmm.trips_completed), 2) AS idle_hours_per_trip,
ROUND(SUM(dmm.on_time_delivery_rate * dmm.trips_completed) / SUM(dmm.trips_completed), 2) AS weighted_avg_on_time
FROM dbo.driver_monthly_metrics dmm
JOIN dbo.drivers dri
ON dmm.driver_id = dri.driver_id
GROUP BY dmm.driver_id, CONCAT(dri.first_name, ' ', dri.last_name)
)

SELECT 
ROUND(SUM(weighted_avg_on_time * total_trips_completed) / SUM(total_trips_completed), 2) AS fleet_avg_on_time,
ROUND(SUM(weighted_avg_mpg * total_trips_completed) / SUM(total_trips_completed), 2) AS fleet_avg_mpg,
ROUND(SUM(idle_hours_per_trip * total_trips_completed) / SUM(total_trips_completed), 2) AS fleet_avg_idle_hours
FROM efficiency_avgs

/* FINDINGS:
Fleet Average MPG:                6.50
Fleet Average Idle Hours:         7 hours
Fleet Average On Time Delivery:   45%

Data indicates that on average, drivers perform similarly other than a few outliers based on average on time delivery. 
Outliers: Lowest Performer: Mary Wilson (37% on time), Highest Performer: Jessica Johnson (50% on time)

45% fleet on time rate showcases need for further analysis to identify whether this is a 
systemic or indiviudal efficiency issue. 

Idle hours per trip requires deeper analysis to determine whether lengthened idle hours are caused by route conditions or individual driver behavior. 
Recommended analysis includes: routes, traffic patterns, weather events, loading station wait times. 

